The paper deals with languages of words indexed by countable linear orderings, which is a topic in logic and automata theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algebraic notions of recognizability, which is related to formal language theory and automata theory, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also has applications in monadic second-order logic, which is a topic in computational complexity theory, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves the MSO-definability of sets of rational numbers and trees, which are topics in formal languages and graph theory, respectively, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible sub-categories as well.
